Month
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Crimestoppers of Greater New Orleans (GNO) on the occasion of its
3 forty-fifth anniversary and to recognize March 2026 as Louisiana Crimestoppers
4 Month.
5 WHEREAS, crime creates a path of destruction that changes lives and causes
6 emotional trauma, destroying the foundation for public safety and quality of life;
7 Louisianians stand strong in their beliefs to use everything legally in our power to ensure
8 that our communities are not victimized by criminals and that those who commit criminal
9 acts are brought to justice under state and federal laws; and
10 WHEREAS, Crimestoppers GNO and its board of directors take a stand against
11 crime by bringing together citizens, law enforcement, media, businesses, and educational
12 institutions to combat crime and make communities safer in Orleans, Jefferson, St. Bernard,
13 St. Charles, St. John the Baptist, St. James, St. Tammany, Plaquemines, and Washington
14 parishes and through its Safe Schools LA program that covers schools throughout Louisiana;
15 and
16 WHEREAS, Crimestoppers GNO has created an effective system for solving crimes
17 and has helped citizens take back control of their neighborhoods by utilizing media
18 awareness, an anonymous tip process, and relationships with local, state, and federal law
19 enforcement; and
