1 WHEREAS, Crimestoppers GNO was chartered as a nonprofit organization in
2 December 1981; the organization focuses on community engagement, anonymity, support
3 for law enforcement, building relationships, and providing victim support; the organization's
4 efforts have resulted in over one hundred thousand tips, nearly twenty-seven thousand felony
5 arrests, and more than $2,785,650 in cash rewards for tipsters; and
6 WHEREAS, in 2025, Crimestoppers GNO worked alongside the Louisiana State
7 Police and other local and federal agencies to assist in the investigation of the May 16th
8 escape of ten inmates from the New Orleans Parish Justice Center; the organization offered
9 cash rewards and provided the public the ability to report several thousand tips
10 anonymously, which led to the capture of several inmates; and
11 WHEREAS, Crimestoppers GNO is affiliated with Crimestoppers USA and serves
12 a mission to provide law enforcement with information on crimes; these efforts increase
13 arrests in our community and lead to greater public awareness of safety issues and crime
14 prevention.
15 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
16 commend Crimestoppers GNO on the occasion of its forty-fifth anniversary; does hereby
17 recognize March 2026 as Louisiana Crimestoppers Month; and does hereby encourage all
18 residents to participate in local Crimestoppers efforts to prevent crime and strengthen the
19 state's communities.
